  "prompt": "Does any member of a Instagram group see the message I send?",
  "response": "When you send a message in an Instagram group chat, **all members of the group** can see the message unless they have left the group or been removed. Here\u2019s how it works:\n\n1. **Group Visibility**: The message is visible to everyone in the group unless someone has explicitly left or been removed.\n2. **Notifications**: Members will receive notifications about the message unless they have muted the conversation.\n3. **Privacy**: Instagram group chats are private, so only the members of the group can see the messages\u2014no one outside the group can access them.\n4. **Message Deletion**: If you delete a message, it will disappear for everyone in the group, but they may still see a notification that a message was deleted.\n\nIf you want to send a message that only specific people can see, you\u2019ll need to create a separate direct message or group chat with just those individuals.",
